    {
      "type": "articles",
      "specificArticles": [
        {
          "textContent": "Start from Casa Petri and head to the Limestone Sculptures from the Orlea area and then to pasture lands where the locals leave their cattle to graze. From here you will have to go down in the valley at the Carpiniș Regional Center. Then you will have to climb back along the Vârtop and Gârda-Bărbulești villages. On this section of the trail you will find at the end of summer areas with raspberries, wild strawberries and blackberries. Next destination is the Rotundu Peak, a place that offers an amazing view to Rosia Montana village. Return back home along the Țarinii lake. The trail is on unpaved roads and is perfect for hiking or mountain bikes.",
